ID... He continued that they just came from battle in [northern Myanmar] and said their blood was still boiling. He threatened us that if we are going to do any wrong, they would shoot [us] directly. He continued that we would have to follow whatever they say to us, so that we can live in the country. And he started threatening [us] to take the NVC.\u0026quot;\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/blockquote\u003e \u003cfigcaption\u003eRohingya leader from Chut Pyin\u003c/figcaption\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure\u003e \u003cblockquote class= \"testimony\"\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u0026quot;There were around 30 of us Rohingya leaders, the Rakhine Village Administrators, and BGP officers [who] participated in meeting. And the captain of the military started introducing that they are from [LID] 33 based in Sagaing… He also told us they came from battle…and he continued that there are two [LIDs], 33 and 99, [that came to] northern Rakhine State. He said, ‘We are the two meanest battalions in the Myanmar military.’ He threatened us that they would show us how they are the meanest if we did any wrong.\u0026quot;\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/blockquote\u003e \u003cfigcaption\u003eRohingya leader from Zay Di Pyin\u003c/figcaption\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e","unique_id":"03_military_03"},{"animation":true,"animation_layers":[{"id":"04_testimony","method":"fade_in","type":"point"}],"detail":{"chapter":"Intense Violence","end_date":"","long_description":"These threats become a reality on 27 August, just days after ARSA attacked security posts across the region. That afternoon, Myanmar security forces, working with local vigilantes, surrounded and deliberately attacked the Rohingya in Chut Pyin.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eSoldiers pulled Rohingya men and boys from their homes and executed them or took them away, never to be seen again;\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eRaped women outside their homes or in the schoolhouse;\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e And opened fire on people 