\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eDeportation or forcible transfer\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ePersecution\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eThe crime of apartheid\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eEnforced disappearance  and\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eOther inhumane acts, including forced starvation\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eCrimes against humanity are exactly what the term suggests--crimes so serious that they are the concern not only of their victims, survivors, and the states in question, but of humanity as a whole.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e","moment_date":"","short_description":"","start_date":"","title":""},"full_screen":true,"interactive_layers":[],"layers":[],"map":{"before_after":false,"before_style":"","interactive":false,"load_new_basemap":false,"settings":{"center":"93.223,19.488","controls":false,"mapbox_style":"mapbox://styles/situmapping/cjhax0pbm02js2sqljey5qnpr","max_bounds":[[87.71,15.72],[100.45,24.44]],"max_zoom":"","min_zoom":"","style_name":"06_remaking","zoom":"6.5"},"zoom_duration":""},"narrative_content":"","unique_id":"06_remaking_05"},{"animation":false,"animation_layers":[],"detail":{"chapter":"Take Action","end_date":"","long_description":"\u003cdiv class=\"full_screen_text\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eBring the Myanmar Military to Justice\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eResponsibility for what happened to the Rohingya in northern Rakhine State goes all the way to the top of the Myanmar military. In our \u003ca href=\"https://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/asa16/8630/2018/en/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003elatest\u003c/a\u003e report, we have identified 13 individuals suspected of playing a key role in these crimes, either as direct perpetrators or under command responsibility.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure class=\"take_action_fig\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/amnesty-rohingya/report_media/06_remaking/GettyImages-517718512+-+Min+Aung+Hlaing_med.jpg\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/amnesty-rohingya/report_media/06_remaking/GettyImages-5177